    {
      "title": "Substitute for y",
      "content": "Use $y=6x+16$ in the second equation.<br/>$$-7x-y=36$$<br/>$$-7x-(6x+16)=36$$",
      "desmosExpressions": [
        "y=6x+16",
        "y=-7x-36"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for x",
      "content": "Combine like terms and isolate $x$.<br/>$$-13x-16=36$$<br/>$$-13x=52$$<br/>$$x=-4$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the y-coordinate",
      "content": "Substitute $x=-4$ into $y=6x+16$.<br/>$$y=6(-4)+16=-8$$<br/>So the solution is $(-4,-8)$.<br/>The answer is <strong>A</strong>."
    }
